<p>This project is a direct descendant of the work of two people: <a href="http://daviddarts.com/">Dr. David Darts</a>, founder of the <a href="http://wiki.daviddarts.com/PirateBox">Piratebox project</a>, and <a href="https://twitter.com/MatthiasStrubel">Matthias Strubel</a>, one of the lead developers for Piratebox. Matthias has been patient, thoughtful, and an amazing resource when I ran into roadblocks. Thanks to both of you for helping make LibraryBox possible. </p>

<p>Unending thanks to my wife Betsy and daughter Eliza for putting up with the long hours and for all the support. LibraryBox v2.0 would not have been possible without the support of the Kickstarter Backers, all of whom are listed below.  Thanks to <a href="https://twitter.com/giantlibrarian">Matt Neer</a> at the <a href="http://www.lakeforestlibrary.org/about-the-library/user-guides.html?layout=edit&id=327">Lake Forest Library</a> for the inspiration about the documentation on the 0.3.2 Piratebox release. I’d also like to thank <a href="https://twitter.com/rsinger">Ross Singer</a> for the coding help when I knew that something was possible but didn’t have the language needed to do it, and <a href="http://andromedayelton.com/">Andromeda Yelton</a> for yet more coding help, editing, and making sure I didn’t sound like an idiot (much), and to <a href="http://www.blyberg.net/">John Blyberg</a> for swooping in at the last minute. Finally, thanks to Bo Baker, cinematographer extraordinaire, who helped me shoot the video, and has been a great brainstorming partner with this thing.</p>

